## Multi-Brain Usage

If you have multiple brain packs installed, you can target specific brains with any skill using `--brain-slug` flags.

### Syntax

```
/skill-name --brain-slug "Your question"
/skill-name --brain-1 --brain-2 "Your question"    # multi-brain mode
/skill-name "Your question"                          # default brain (auto if only one installed)
```

### Examples

```
/advise --scott-belsky "Should I pivot to enterprise?"
/advise --paul-graham "Should I pivot to enterprise?"
/advise --scott-belsky --paul-graham "Should I pivot to enterprise?"
/brainfight --scott-belsky --paul-graham "How to hire well"
/mashup --scott-belsky --paul-graham "taste + startups"
```

### How It Works

- **Single brain installed:** No flag needed — skills use the only brain available.
- **Multiple brains, no flag:** Skills list available brains and ask which to use.
- **One flag:** Skills consult that specific brain.
- **Two+ flags:** Skills run against each brain independently, then synthesize perspectives showing agreements and tensions.

### Skills That Shine in Multi-Brain Mode

- **/brainfight** — Pit thinkers head-to-head on any topic. The killer feature.
- **/mashup** — Cross-brain synthesis produces insights no single brain contains.
- **/connect** — Cross-brain bridges are the highest-value connections.
- **/debate** — Multiple challengers stress-test your thinking from different angles.
- **/teach** — Same concept explained from different worldviews reveals hidden assumptions.

### Universal Skills Location

Universal skills (brain-agnostic) are at `pack/universal-skills/`. Per-brain skills remain in each brain's pack directory for backwards compatibility.

